# official-site-cms Architecture Plan

## 1) Module structure and file organization

- `app/(public)/`
  - Public routes: `/`, `/about`, `/blog`, `/blog/[slug]`
  - Public layout and site-wide metadata defaults
- `app/(admin)/`
  - Auth route: `/login`
  - Protected admin routes under `/admin` (dashboard, posts, pages, media)
- `app/api/`
  - Auth handler (`auth/[...nextauth]`)
  - Upload endpoints (`upload`, `uploads/[...path]`)
- `components/admin/`
  - Admin-only UI components (sidebar, forms, logout, media list)
- `components/site/`
  - Public marketing/blog UI components (header/footer/sections/cards/renderers)
- `components/ui/`
  - shadcn/ui shared primitives
- `actions/`
  - Server Actions grouped by domain (`posts.ts`, `pages.ts`, later `media.ts` if needed)
- `lib/`
  - Shared infrastructure/utilities:
    - `db.ts` (Prisma singleton)
    - `auth.ts` + `lib/auth.ts` helpers
    - `markdown.ts` (render helpers: GFM, reading time, syntax setup)
    - `structured-data.ts` (JSON-LD builders)
    - `utils.ts` (shadcn class helpers)
- `prisma/`
  - `schema.prisma`, migrations, `seed.ts`
- root infra/config
  - `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `.env.example`, `.dockerignore`

## 2) Shared types and data model baseline

Prisma models:
- `User`: `id`, `email` (unique), `passwordHash`, `role` (`ADMIN`), timestamps
- `BlogPost`: `id`, `title`, `slug` (unique), `excerpt`, `bodyMarkdown`, `coverImageUrl`, `status` (`DRAFT|PUBLISHED`), `publishedAt`, timestamps
- `PageContent`: `id`, `slug` (unique: `about`, `landing`), `title`, `bodyMarkdown`, `sectionsJson` (JSON for landing editable blocks), timestamps
- `Media`: `id`, `filename`, `path`, `mimeType`, `size`, `alt`, timestamps

Type strategy:
- Keep source-of-truth types in Prisma-generated client.
- Add lightweight domain DTO types in `lib/types.ts` only for UI forms/view models when Prisma shape should not be exposed directly.
- Use Zod schemas per form/action (posts/pages/login/upload) for validation and typed error maps.

## 3) Dependencies between issues (execution graph)

Foundation:
- #1 Next.js scaffold is prerequisite for most work.
- #2 UI system and #3 Prisma can proceed after #1.
- #4 Docker and #5 Auth depend on #1 + #3.

Admin/auth chain:
- #6 login, #7 middleware, #8 admin shell depend on #5.
- #9 post list/delete depends on #8 + #3.
- #10 post create/edit depends on #9 + #3.
- #11 media upload depends on #8 + #3.
- #12 page content editor depends on #8 + #3.

Public site chain:
- #13 public layout depends on #1 + #2.
- #14 and #15 depend on #13 (and should read CMS fallback data shape from #12).
- #16 About depends on #12 data model + markdown utils.
- #17 blog listing depends on #10 publish flow.
- #18 blog detail depends on #10 + markdown renderer.
- #19 metadata/sitemap/robots depends on #17/#18.

Hardening/finalization:
- #20 error/loading states should follow route implementation.
- #21 responsive/polish follows all UI features.
- #22 seed/docs/deployment finalizes after infra + app features are stable.

## 4) Key design decisions

- Next.js 15 App Router with route groups `(public)` and `(admin)` to separate concerns without URL noise.
- Server-first rendering for data pages; use client components only for interactive forms/editor UX.
- Auth.js v5 credentials with Prisma-backed admin user and bcrypt password hashes.
- Centralized route protection in `middleware.ts` for `/admin/*` with explicit allowlist for `/login` and auth callbacks.
- Server Actions for admin CRUD to keep write logic co-located and reduce API surface; use API routes only for file upload/serve.
- Local uploads stored in `/uploads` and indexed in `Media` table; Docker volume mount preserves files.
- Markdown pipeline shared in `lib/markdown.ts` to avoid duplicate rendering config between About and Blog.
- CMS fallback policy: public pages render DB content if present, else deterministic defaults from code.
- SEO as first-class: per-post metadata generation, sitemap from published posts only, robots allow crawl.
- Keep implementation order strict by issue dependencies to avoid rework between sessions.
